# Phase 3B -- THE HEADLINE: gpt3b (~2.78B) over real wikitext. DP replicates the
# FULL model on EVERY node, and its fp32 Adam state (~44GB) far exceeds the 24GB
# Mac (and leaves no headroom on the 48GB Mac either), so data parallelism CANNOT
# train it -- only the split can. memory-aware cut: rank0(48GB)~29.8GB state,
# rank1(24GB)~14.6GB.
# Sourced by scripts/run_mac_48gb.sh / run_mac_24gb.sh. SAME bytes on both Macs.
#
# If rank0 OOMs on the 48GB Mac, lower MACLUSTER_BATCH_SIZE (4, then 2) or
# MACLUSTER_SEQ_LEN -- that shrinks activations; the param/optimizer state is fixed.
MACLUSTER_TASK=wikitext
MACLUSTER_MODEL=gpt3b
MACLUSTER_PARALLELISM=pipeline
MACLUSTER_STAGE_MEM_GB=48,24
MACLUSTER_N_MICRO=4
MACLUSTER_MAX_STEPS=20
MACLUSTER_BATCH_SIZE=8
MACLUSTER_SEQ_LEN=128
MACLUSTER_INNER_OPT=adam
MACLUSTER_INNER_LR=0.0003
MACLUSTER_LINK=wifi
MACLUSTER_EVAL_EVERY=5
MACLUSTER_SEED=0
MACLUSTER_RUNS_ROOT=runs

CLUSTER=mac_3b
N=2
